# Visual Studio build output
Debug/
Release/
x64/
x86/
*.exe
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.obj
*.lib
*.exp

# Visual Studio files
.vs/
*.user
*.suo
*.sdf
*.opensdf
*.VC.db
*.VC.opendb
*.ipch

# Visual Studio solution/project (keep these — they're needed)
# *.sln
# *.vcxproj
# *.vcxproj.filters

# Compiled output
ipch/
*.tlog
*.lastbuildstate
*.unsuccessfulbuild
```

The important ones are `.vs/` and `x64/` — those are the bulk of the size. The `.vs/` folder alone can be hundreds of MB.

After adding this, if you've already committed those folders you'll need to remove them from tracking:
```
git rm -r --cached .vs/
git rm -r --cached x64/
git commit -m "remove build artifacts from tracking"